  "text": "b) Decomposition during coevolution: Yang et al. [CITATION_1] incorporate a random grouping strategy with differential evolutionary cooperative coevolution (DECC). In the resultant algorithm termed DECC-G, according to the random grouping strategy, a problem is dynamically decomposed into a fixed number of subcomponents by randomly allocating decision variables to the subcomponents in every generation. DECC-G have been extended to improve random grouping. For example, in DECC-ML [CITATION_2] (DECC with a modified multilevel cooperative coevolution technique extended from [CITATION_3] ) more frequent random grouping was suggested. a CC particle swarm optimization [CITATION_4] adopts an adaptive scheme to dynamically determine the subcomponent sizes for random grouping during a run. Very recently, Kabán et al. [CITATION_5] introduced an ensemble of random projections to solve LSO within the framework of EDA with fixed subcomponent sizes.",
